        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 7:29PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Putnam, or 12 miles east of Butler, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Putnam, Nanafalia, Sweet Water, and Nicholsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
